From 3fb5d1b7bb5ebab51e76bf5d5dafeaede3546c9c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GloriousEggroll <gloriouseggroll@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 15:59:16 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] mfreadwrite: make source reader video playback resilient
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Rework SourceReader stream scheduling, transform draining, async seek/flush handling, EOS reporting, timestamp rebasing, and stream replacement so games that drive Media Foundation in nonstandard ways can keep video and audio moving without SteamGameId hacks.

Important behavior covered by this change:

- Halo Infinite no longer hangs where startup videos should play.

- Darksiders Warmastered Edition can read EOS from all selected Windows Media streams instead of stopping after one stream finishes, replacing the old Darksiders SteamGameId EOS workaround.

- The Medium uses coherent async seek/flush behavior instead of the old SteamGameId-specific Flush() ignore path.

- Persona 5 Strikers and Akiba's Trip avoid the hang/fast-forward regressions caused by stale responses and timestamp jumps after seeks or stream replacement.

- Ys Origin and Ys Origin Demo keep their movie stream timing and frame delivery instead of misrendering/skipping playback after the rebase.

- Nukitashi 2 keeps video frames moving with audio instead of falling back to audio-only black-screen playback.

- WRC4 can advance through clips that previously showed only first/last frames.

- Fable and Resident Evil 1 Remaster keep their movie transitions moving by using the same stream replacement, EOS, and timestamp cleanup paths instead of stale queued samples.

- Ninja Gaiden Sigma benefits from the same source-reader draining and seek/flush ordering fixes used by the other startup-video regressions.

- I Can't Win Against Those Pretty Girls [我打不过漂亮的她们] keeps pause/play responsive after repeated rapid toggles by keeping async seek and flush state coherent.

- Biomutant can transition out of its intro video sequence without relying on the old SteamGameId path.

- Warhammer 40,000: Dakka Squadron keeps its Vorbis/AAC media-source path working through general media type handling instead of a SteamGameId fake-AAC branch.

The media-source side adds the event/state information needed by the reader to distinguish pending async starts, stream end, presentation end, and source replacement.
